Smart enumerations are a design pattern that combines the benefits of traditional enumerations with the flexibility of classes. They are often used in Domain-Driven Design (DDD) applications to represent domain-specific concepts.

**Example: Order Status Enum**

Let's consider an example of an `OrderStatus` smart enumeration:
```csharp
public abstract class OrderStatus
{
    public string Name { get; }
    public string Description { get; }

    protected OrderStatus(string name, string description)
    {
        Name = name;
        Description = description;
    }

    public abstract void Apply(Order order);
}

public class PendingOrderStatus : OrderStatus
{
    public PendingOrderStatus() 
        : base("Pending", "Order is pending payment") { }

    public override void Apply(Order order)
    {
        // Update order status to pending
        order.Status = this;
    }
}

public class ShippedOrderStatus : OrderStatus
{
    public ShippedOrderStatus() 
        : base("Shipped", "Order has been shipped") { }

    public override void Apply(Order order)
    {
        // Update order status to shipped
        order.Status = this;
    }
}

